1
00:00:12,547 --> 00:00:16,049
Bunny... [breathing heavily]
...I want this on camera.

2
00:00:16,818 --> 00:00:18,853
I have something important
to say.

3
00:00:21,088 --> 00:00:23,825
All right, Dad. I'm recording.

4
00:00:23,858 --> 00:00:26,961
There's a secret
I've been keeping for ten years,

5
00:00:27,494 --> 00:00:30,130
and I need
to get it off my chest.

6
00:00:30,163 --> 00:00:31,498
Dad.

7
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:33,001
Let me say this, Son.

8
00:00:34,002 --> 00:00:36,169
It's time the truth came out.

9
00:00:37,304 --> 00:00:38,338
Thanksgiving.

10
00:00:39,139 --> 00:00:40,307
Ten years ago.

11
00:00:41,408 --> 00:00:42,844
It was me.

12
00:00:42,877 --> 00:00:44,444
[panting]

13
00:00:44,478 --> 00:00:45,880
I killed Barry.

14
00:00:45,914 --> 00:00:47,782
Grandpa. No.

15
00:00:47,815 --> 00:00:49,817
When you all were in bed,

16
00:00:49,851 --> 00:00:53,521
I waited for Barry at the top
of the basement stairs,

17
00:00:53,555 --> 00:00:56,423
and I pushed him to his death.

18
00:00:56,991 --> 00:01:00,662
And then, I moved his body
into the sauna,

19
00:01:00,695 --> 00:01:04,532
hoping that it would all
be written off as an accident.

20
00:01:04,566 --> 00:01:05,833
That's not true, darling.

21
00:01:05,867 --> 00:01:09,037
It is true.
And it's time I admit it.

22
00:01:25,753 --> 00:01:27,989
[Morgan] Morgan Gillory, LAPD.

23
00:01:28,022 --> 00:01:29,156
[Karadec sighs]

24
00:01:29,189 --> 00:01:31,358
Freeze.
Morgan Gillory, Major Crimes.

25
00:01:32,125 --> 00:01:33,628
It worked. You're frozen.

26
00:01:34,361 --> 00:01:36,864
Give me that.
Where did you get this?

27
00:01:36,898 --> 00:01:38,365
Checkout at the Dollar Store.

28
00:01:38,398 --> 00:01:40,602
Turns out anyone can be a cop
if you wait in line long enough.

29
00:01:40,635 --> 00:01:41,869
Chloe couldn't resist.

30
00:01:41,903 --> 00:01:43,337
There should be a law
against these things.

31
00:01:43,370 --> 00:01:45,439
That's what I was about to say.
It's an absolute outrage.

32
00:01:46,874 --> 00:01:49,911
Why is Jon down here with Melon?
He never comes to this floor.

33
00:01:49,944 --> 00:01:51,244
I have no idea.

34
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:52,747
[Lieutenant Melon] Top of
the morning to ya, Selena.

35
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:55,516
[Selena] Melon, Detective Jon.
What can I do for you gentlemen?

36
00:01:55,550 --> 00:01:56,918
[Detective Jon]
Celebrate with us.

37
00:01:56,951 --> 00:01:58,686
We closed a cold case
this morning.

38
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,120
-[Selena] Which one?
-[Lieutenant Melon]
We got a confession

39
00:02:00,153 --> 00:02:01,254
on the Bucket Lane Murder.

40
00:02:02,557 --> 00:02:03,992
[Selena] Who confessed?

41
00:02:04,025 --> 00:02:05,627
[Lieutenant Melon] The guy
Captain and I thought did it.

42
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:08,362
The old man came clean
on his deathbed.

43
00:02:08,395 --> 00:02:10,163
He brought champagne.

44
00:02:10,197 --> 00:02:11,833
Maybe Lieutenant's
getting promoted.

45
00:02:11,866 --> 00:02:14,267
Mm-mmm. Melon wouldn't
ride along for that.

46
00:02:14,301 --> 00:02:15,570
[Detective Jon]
This is a big win.

47
00:02:15,603 --> 00:02:17,404
Some detectives never catch
their white whale.

48
00:02:17,437 --> 00:02:20,508
[Lieutenant Melon] He's right.
Enjoy your champagne.

49
00:02:27,815 --> 00:02:29,282
[chair clatters]

50
00:02:31,052 --> 00:02:32,386
[sighs]

51
00:02:32,419 --> 00:02:33,855
Who has the good scotch?

52
00:02:34,454 --> 00:02:36,223
Morgan Gillory, Liquor Patrol.

53
00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:38,660
-How did you get that back?
-They come in a two-pack.

54
00:02:38,693 --> 00:02:40,061
Lieutenant, what was that about?

55
00:02:40,094 --> 00:02:41,562
The Bucket Lane Murder.

56
00:02:41,596 --> 00:02:43,865
George Donovan confessed
on his deathbed.

57
00:02:44,532 --> 00:02:45,667
A decade later?

58
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:47,835
Bucket Lane Murder.

59
00:02:47,869 --> 00:02:49,971
Sounds familiar,
but the details are fuzzy.

60
00:02:50,004 --> 00:02:52,140
Morgan Gillory is fuzzy
on the details?

61
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:55,109
It was in the news for months.
Were you living under a rock
in 2014?

62
00:02:55,143 --> 00:02:57,812
-[Young Ava drumming
continuously]
-Sorry. Sorry.

63
00:02:58,345 --> 00:02:59,847
Ooh, whoops.

64
00:02:59,881 --> 00:03:01,549
I would've killed
for a rock to live under.

65
00:03:02,517 --> 00:03:05,620
It was murder in a mansion?
Or something about a sauna?

66
00:03:05,653 --> 00:03:07,155
Melon and I were
junior detectives.

67
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:08,723
He liked George for it.

68
00:03:08,756 --> 00:03:11,491
I had reservations.
George beat the case.

69
00:03:11,526 --> 00:03:12,794
But he confesses now?

70
00:03:12,827 --> 00:03:14,394
Now I need to know
the whole story.

71
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,165
Follow me.

72
00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:19,834
Day after Thanksgiving 2014,

73
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:22,036
Heather Donovan's husband,
Barry Johnson,

74
00:03:22,670 --> 00:03:24,539
was murdered in the family home.

75
00:03:24,572 --> 00:03:26,941
The housekeeper found him
in the sauna,

76
00:03:26,974 --> 00:03:29,010
slow-cooked like Texas barbecue.

77
00:03:30,745 --> 00:03:33,181
The family assumed
that Barry fell asleep

78
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,749
during his nightly shvitz.

79
00:03:34,782 --> 00:03:37,952
But the autopsy revealed
cause of death
to be a broken neck.

80
00:03:37,985 --> 00:03:39,954
He was dead
before he went into the sauna.

81
00:03:39,987 --> 00:03:42,322
Yeah, the theory was the killer
pushed Barry down the stairs,

82
00:03:42,355 --> 00:03:43,691
breaking his neck,

83
00:03:43,725 --> 00:03:45,225
then placed him in the sauna
to cover up the crime.

84
00:03:45,258 --> 00:03:47,695
Hoping it'd be written off as
an intoxicated man passing out

85
00:03:47,729 --> 00:03:48,796
and dehydrating in there.

86
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:50,164
Lenore, George's wife, said

87
00:03:50,198 --> 00:03:52,767
she saw Barry heading
to the basement in his robe

88
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,001
shortly after midnight.

89
00:03:54,035 --> 00:03:55,536
That's the last time
anyone saw him alive.

90
00:03:55,570 --> 00:03:58,606
Everyone's in bed and claimed
not to have heard anything,

91
00:03:58,639 --> 00:04:01,509
but a drop of Barry's blood was
found on one of George's shirts

92
00:04:01,542 --> 00:04:03,111
stuffed in the laundry hamper.

93
00:04:03,144 --> 00:04:06,080
This is why he ended up
in the defendant's chair.

94
00:04:06,114 --> 00:04:08,783
I thought it was a weak case,
but the DA ran with it.

95
00:04:08,816 --> 00:04:10,718
Ultimately,
there wasn't enough to convict

96
00:04:10,752 --> 00:04:12,285
because of the coke dealer.

97
00:04:12,854 --> 00:04:14,088
There's a coke dealer too?

98
00:04:14,122 --> 00:04:15,690
Billy Ross.

99
00:04:15,723 --> 00:04:19,026
He's dead now. He was pulled
over for running a stop sign

100
00:04:19,060 --> 00:04:21,495
shortly after midnight in
his gold 442,

101
00:04:21,529 --> 00:04:22,997
five blocks from the murder.

102
00:04:23,030 --> 00:04:24,632
And Barry had cocaine
in his system.

103
00:04:24,665 --> 00:04:27,535
The defense presented
this far-fetched theory

104
00:04:27,568 --> 00:04:29,070
that Billy Ross
broke into the house,

105
00:04:29,103 --> 00:04:31,038
killed Barry
after a drug deal gone wrong

106
00:04:31,072 --> 00:04:32,673
when we never found any proof

107
00:04:32,707 --> 00:04:35,009
that Billy Ross was ever
even at the house.

108
00:04:35,042 --> 00:04:38,179
George got off, but Melon always
believed he was the killer.

109
00:04:38,212 --> 00:04:39,312
Why didn't you?

110
00:04:41,314 --> 00:04:43,217
Gut instinct.
It just didn't add up.

111
00:04:43,251 --> 00:04:44,585
George was well-liked.

112
00:04:44,619 --> 00:04:46,988
He never had
any history of violence.

113
00:04:47,021 --> 00:04:48,556
He was a philanthropist.

114
00:04:48,589 --> 00:04:50,858
He was a bigwig
at the chamber of commerce.

115
00:04:50,892 --> 00:04:54,095
He spearheaded that whole
affordable housing initiative.

116
00:04:54,128 --> 00:04:55,495
So he didn't seem
like a murderer.

117
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:56,731
That was part of it.

118
00:04:56,764 --> 00:04:58,666
I also didn't buy
that a 70-something-year-old man

119
00:04:58,699 --> 00:05:01,035
with a hip replacement could
carry Barry into the sauna.

120
00:05:01,068 --> 00:05:02,703
Well, Barry was
a little guy though.

121
00:05:02,737 --> 00:05:03,604
Still.

122
00:05:04,337 --> 00:05:05,640
So what's your gut say now?

123
00:05:09,243 --> 00:05:12,445
The aftermath of the crime
has been brutal on the Donovans.

124
00:05:12,479 --> 00:05:14,447
They used to be
the most well-respected family

125
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:16,551
in Beverly Hills
for their ties to politics

126
00:05:16,584 --> 00:05:19,386
and a charity for domestic
violence victims in their name.

127
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:21,289
And suddenly overnight,

128
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:24,158
half of America believes one
of them has to be a murderer.

129
00:05:24,826 --> 00:05:27,094
Now George confesses
to the crime?

130
00:05:27,128 --> 00:05:29,063
I think he did it
to clear his family.

131
00:05:29,096 --> 00:05:31,265
He wanted them to be able
to lead normal lives.

132
00:05:31,299 --> 00:05:32,733
Who do you think did it?

133
00:05:35,435 --> 00:05:36,871
I don't know.

134
00:05:38,172 --> 00:05:40,708
Thank you for joining me
on this trip down memory lane.

135
00:05:42,944 --> 00:05:44,245
Yeah.

136
00:05:46,446 --> 00:05:48,448
Sure you don't want me
to track down that scotch?

137
00:05:48,481 --> 00:05:51,552
No. But there's something
you can do for me.

138
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:56,423
Every cop has that one case they
can't get out of their head,

139
00:05:56,456 --> 00:05:57,625
and this one's mine.

140
00:05:58,826 --> 00:06:01,128
I regret not following my gut
ten years ago.

141
00:06:01,162 --> 00:06:02,530
Why didn't you?

142
00:06:02,563 --> 00:06:04,799
I let Melon talk me out
of going deeper on my hunch.

143
00:06:04,832 --> 00:06:07,501
I felt like
I had to toe the line,

144
00:06:07,535 --> 00:06:09,837
be one of the boys
for the sake of my career.

145
00:06:11,739 --> 00:06:14,041
I am embarrassed
I let that happen.

146
00:06:20,982 --> 00:06:23,017
Mind seeing
if there's something we missed?

147
00:06:26,587 --> 00:06:27,588
On it, boss.

